[Distribution of the species-specific lifespan in various taxonomic animal 
groups].

[Article in Russian]

Muradian KhK.

A distribution of specific lifespan has been studied in different taxonomic 
groups of animals. A positive skewness has been observed in animal kingdom as 
well as in smaller taxonomic groups. The skewness is higher in groups with 
relatively short lifespan (Insecta, Rotatoria, Mollusca). A coefficient of 
variation and excess is also higher in the above groups. A comparison of these 
coefficients with paleontological age of the group allows to conclude that 
evolutionary progress of animals was accompanied by the increase in skewness, 
variation and excess of specific lifespan distribution.

