statistics as a proxy for hospital treatment costs.

St Leger AS(1).

Author information:
(1)Department of Community Medicine, University of Manchester, UK.

The long-term effects upon acute-care hospital costs of reductions of morbidity 
and mortality from various causes are explored. The daily number of beds used 
per million population for all diagnostic categories is suggested as a proxy 
measure of hospital costs. An index of lifetime bed usage for a hypothetical 
